race.comment: SHOW ME THE STARS (8) got back at the Sunshine Coast last start but finished off strongly to finish 1.4L off the winner. The senior hoop replaces the apprentice now and Philpot has a good record on board. Can sit handy from the draw this time and can play a leading role. ZIMBARA (7) led them up at the Sunny Coast most recently and did take catching, beaten 0.9L when caught late. Back to this grade seems a good move and she's a track and trip winner previously. Expecting her to be on the speed once again from the inside draw and she'll take catching once again. BRAVARO (5) comes up from NSW where she's been just fair in her past couple. Blinkers go on for the first time now and this does look a touch easier. Form out of her last start has been strong and she can be in the finish. GREY IMPACT (1) can improve with the first-up run under her belt. SONIC ARROW (13) is better than we saw last start and can be in the finish.
